<HEADLINE>
FT  10 FEB 92 / By-election blow for Japan's Miyazawa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Opposition parties joined forces to defeat Japan's ruling party in a closely
watched upper house by-election yesterday, Reuter reports from Tokyo. The
defeat dealt a heavy blow to Prime Minister Kiichi Miyazawa's
scandal-plagued government.
The by-election, the first national poll since Mr Miyazawa took office in
November, was seen as a test of public confidence in the new government
ahead of upper house elections due in July. The LDP's defeat came after
almost daily disclosures of political scandals involving close aides of
Miyazawa.
