<HEADLINE>
FT  10 FEB 92 / Observer: Fare Whack
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Inflation is hitting Russia in a big way. Last December a single fare from
Moscow to London cost 2,000 roubles. Now it will set you back 35,000
roubles. A reasonable annual salary is around 8,000 roubles. It seems a high
price for the dubious pleasures of travelling via Aeroflot.
</TEXT>
