FT  08 FEB 92 / UK Company News: Independent Inv Co net assets grow
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Over the six months ended December 31 1991, net asset value at The
Independent Investment Company rose 5 per cent to 57.7p, and in January
moved up a further 11 per cent to 64.1p.
A significant factor in the January rise was the near-doubling in the share
price of the US company Read-Rite, which is now Independent's largest
holding.
It became so as a result of its public offering and subsequent share price
performance. It meant that Independent's unlisted investments at December 31
represented 51 per cent of total assets, against 64 per cent at end-June.
In the interim period total revenue was again Pounds 1.5m, but heavier
interest charges and expenses cut earnings per share to 0.4p (0.59p).
