FT  08 FEB 92 / International Company News: Caterpillar to end lock-out
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BARBARA DURR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CATERPILLAR, the world's largest maker of earth-moving and construction
equipment, announced it would end its lock-out of 5,600 workers in an
attempt to resolve its labour dispute with the United Auto Workers, writes
Barbara Durr.
The company asked the union to return to the bargaining table during the
week of February 17. Formal talks broke off over three months ago. The
lock-out occurred on November 7 in retaliation for a partial strike
involving 2,400 UAW members that began on November 3.
Caterpillar said it will put 'important modifications' to its contract
proposal on the table. The UAW has demanded Caterpillar match its recent
contract deal with Deere &amp; Co, heavy equipment maker.
