<HEADLINE>
FT  08 FEB 92 / Phone bills lower in France
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UK TELEPHONE charges are more expensive than those in France, about the same
as in Germany but cheaper than in Italy, according to figures published
yesterday by Oftel, the industry regulator.
The figures compare representative residential and business phone bills
using BT, with the cost of the same services in the three other large
European economies.
Residential bills are 22 per cent lower in France, 1 per cent lower in
Germany and 5 per cent higher in Italy. Business bills are 8 per cent lower
in France, 1 per cent lower in Germany but 33 per cent higher in Italy
according to Oftel.
