<TEXT>
Sir, Your article, 'My cheque is in the post. . .', (February 1) caused me
to reflect, not for the first time, on the high-handedness of companies
which give their shareholders little option but to pay for rights issues by
cheque, sent of course at the shareholder's risk. If the safest method of
transferring money is through the inter-bank giro system, why do not
